title: Aparna Yadav pays a visit to Harmandir Sahib Gurudwara in Patna
text:
Aparna Yadav pays a visit to Harmandir Sahib Gurudwara in Patna Aparna visited the Patna Sahib Gurudwara along with Hema Yadav, RJD chief's fifth daughter. Aparna Yadav with Hema Yadav Highlights Aparna arrived here in the morning and went to RJD supremo Lalu Prasad's official bungalow. 2 Later, she visited the Patna Sahib gurudwara along with Hema Yadav, RJD chief's fifth daughter. 3 She spent over 30 minutes at the gurudwara. 
Samajwadi Party patriarch Mulayam Singh Yadav's younger daughter-in-law Aparna Yadav made a surprise visit to Patna. The purpose of Aparna's visit was to visit the Harmandir Sahib Gurudwara in Patna Sahib. 
Aparna arrived here in the morning on Sunday and went to RJD supremo Lalu Prasad's official bungalow 10, Circular Road. After spending some time at Lalu's residence, Aparna visited the Patna Sahib gurudwara along with Hema Yadav, RJD chief's fifth daughter. 
She spent over 30 minutes at the gurudwara. 
Aparna Yadav is making her electoral debut in the Uttar Pradesh elections and is contesting from Lucknow Cantonment seat from where she is fighting against veteran politician and BJP candidate Rita Bahuguna Joshi.
